<TITLE> 20 injured in JaU clashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 20 (bdnews24.com) - Twenty people including four police were injured on Monday in a clash between Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal, Bangladesh Chhatra League and the police in the capital's Jagannath University. "We are maintaining the highest caution. We are ready to handle any untoward situation," the proctor said. The trouble was sparked by a dispute between JCD and BCL activists at around 12:45pm. Police came on campus with batons and tear gas to disperse the angry students. The clashes became violent as the two groups jointly attacked the police. After police retreated students vandalised the Science Building and the VC and proctor's offices, protesting police action on the campus. Proctor Kazi Asaduzzaman and top leaders of the student bodies came to the scene and calmed the situation. Additional police were deployed on campus. Kotwali Police Station sub-inspector Abdul Hannan told bdnews24.com: "Our duty is to maintain law and discipline. We did the job during the trouble." JaU JCD president ABM Parvez Reza told bdnews24.com that BCL attacked them without any provocation. But the situation deteriorated due to the police intervention. BCL president Quamrul Hassan Ripon said that JCD obstructed them in their activities. As they tried to resist the clashes occurred. bdnews2
